35u64
36nv50_gr_units(struct nvkm_gr *gr)
37{
38 return nvkm_rd32(gr->engine.subdev.device, 0x1540);
39}

41/*******************************************************************************
42 * Graphics object classes
43 ******************************************************************************/
44
45static int
46nv50_gr_object_bind(struct nvkm_object *object, struct nvkm_gpuobj *parent,
47 int align, struct nvkm_gpuobj **pgpuobj)
48{
49 int ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(object->engine->subdev.device, 16,
50 align, false, parent, pgpuobj);
51 if (ret == 0) {
52 nvkm_kmap(*pgpuobj);
53 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x00, object->oclass);
54 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x04, 0x00000000);
55 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x08, 0x00000000);
56 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x0c, 0x00000000);
57 nvkm_done(*pgpuobj);
58 }
59 return ret;
60}
61
62const struct nvkm_object_func
63nv50_gr_object = {
64 .bind = nv50_gr_object_bind,
65};
66
67/*******************************************************************************
68 * PGRAPH context
69 ******************************************************************************/
70
71static int
72nv50_gr_chan_bind(struct nvkm_object *object, struct nvkm_gpuobj *parent,
73 int align, struct nvkm_gpuobj **pgpuobj)
74{
75 struct nv50_gr *gr = nv50_gr_chan(object)->gr;
76 int ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(gr->base.engine.subdev.device, gr->size,
77 align, true, parent, pgpuobj);
78 if (ret == 0) {
79 nvkm_kmap(*pgpuobj);
80 nv50_grctx_fill(gr->base.engine.subdev.device, *pgpuobj);
81 nvkm_done(*pgpuobj);
82 }
83 return ret;
84}
85
86static const struct nvkm_object_func
87nv50_gr_chan = {
88 .bind = nv50_gr_chan_bind,
89};
90
91int
92nv50_gr_chan_new(struct nvkm_gr *base, struct nvkm_fifo_chan *fifoch,
93 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
94{
95 struct nv50_gr *gr = nv50_gr(base);
96 struct nv50_gr_chan *chan;
97
98 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
99 return -ENOMEM;
100 nvkm_object_ctor(&nv50_gr_chan, oclass, &chan->object);
101 chan->gr = gr;
102 *pobject = &chan->object;
103 return 0;
104}

242static void
243nv50_gr_prop_trap(struct nv50_gr *gr, u32 ustatus_addr, u32 ustatus, u32 tp)
244{
245 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
246 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
247 u32 e0c = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x04);
248 u32 e10 = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x08);
249 u32 e14 = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x0c);
250 u32 e18 = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x10);
251 u32 e1c = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x14);
252 u32 e20 = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x18);
253 u32 e24 = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr + 0x1c);
254 char msg[128];
255
256 /* CUDA memory: l[], g[] or stack. */
257 if (ustatus & 0x00000080) {
258 if (e18 & 0x80000000) {
259 /* g[] read fault? */
260 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_PROP - TP %d - CUDA_FAULT - Global read fault at address %02x%08x\n",
261 tp, e14, e10 | ((e18 >> 24) & 0x1f));
262 e18 &= ~0x1f000000;
263 } else if (e18 & 0xc) {
264 /* g[] write fault? */
265 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_PROP - TP %d - CUDA_FAULT - Global write fault at address %02x%08x\n",
266 tp, e14, e10 | ((e18 >> 7) & 0x1f));
267 e18 &= ~0x00000f80;
268 } else {
269 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_PROP - TP %d - Unknown CUDA fault at address %02x%08x\n",
270 tp, e14, e10);
271 }
272 ustatus &= ~0x00000080;
273 }
274 if (ustatus) {
275 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), nv50_gr_trap_prop, ustatus);
276 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_PROP - TP %d - %08x [%s] - "
277 "Address %02x%08x\n",
278 tp, ustatus, msg, e14, e10);
279 }
280 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_PROP - TP %d - e0c: %08x, e18: %08x, e1c: %08x, e20: %08x, e24: %08x\n",
281 tp, e0c, e18, e1c, e20, e24);
282}
283
284static void
285nv50_gr_mp_trap(struct nv50_gr *gr, int tpid, int display)
286{
287 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
288 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
289 u32 units = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x1540);
290 u32 addr, mp10, status, pc, oplow, ophigh;
291 char msg[128];
292 int i;
293 int mps = 0;
294 for (i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
295 if (!(units & 1 << (i+24)))
296 continue;
297 if (device->chipset < 0xa0)
298 addr = 0x408200 + (tpid << 12) + (i << 7);
299 else
300 addr = 0x408100 + (tpid << 11) + (i << 7);
301 mp10 = nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x10);
302 status = nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x14);
303 if (!status)
304 continue;
305 if (display) {
306 nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x20);
307 pc = nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x24);
308 oplow = nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x70);
309 ophigh = nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x74);
310 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
311 nv50_mp_exec_errors, status);
312 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_MP_EXEC - TP %d MP %d: "
313 "%08x [%s] at %06x warp %d, "
314 "opcode %08x %08x\n",
315 tpid, i, status, msg, pc & 0xffffff,
316 pc >> 24, oplow, ophigh);
317 }
318 nvkm_wr32(device, addr + 0x10, mp10);
319 nvkm_wr32(device, addr + 0x14, 0);
320 mps++;
321 }
322 if (!mps && display)
323 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_MP_EXEC - TP %d: "
324 "No MPs claiming errors?\n", tpid);
325}
326
327static void
328nv50_gr_tp_trap(struct nv50_gr *gr, int type, u32 ustatus_old,
329 u32 ustatus_new, int display, const char *name)
330{
331 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
332 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
333 u32 units = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x1540);
334 int tps = 0;
335 int i, r;
336 char msg[128];
337 u32 ustatus_addr, ustatus;
338 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
339 if (!(units & (1 << i)))
340 continue;
341 if (device->chipset < 0xa0)
342 ustatus_addr = ustatus_old + (i << 12);
343 else
344 ustatus_addr = ustatus_new + (i << 11);
345 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, ustatus_addr) & 0x7fffffff;
346 if (!ustatus)
347 continue;
348 tps++;
349 switch (type) {
350 case 6: /* texture error... unknown for now */
351 if (display) {
352 nvkm_error(subdev, "magic set %d:\n", i);
353 for (r = ustatus_addr + 4; r <= ustatus_addr + 0x10; r += 4)
354 nvkm_error(subdev, "\t%08x: %08x\n", r,
355 nvkm_rd32(device, r));
356 if (ustatus) {
357 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
358 nv50_tex_traps, ustatus);
359 nvkm_error(subdev,
360 "%s - TP%d: %08x [%s]\n",
361 name, i, ustatus, msg);
362 ustatus = 0;
363 }
364 }
365 break;
366 case 7: /* MP error */
367 if (ustatus & 0x04030000) {
368 nv50_gr_mp_trap(gr, i, display);
369 ustatus &= ~0x04030000;
370 }
371 if (ustatus && display) {
372 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
373 nv50_mpc_traps, ustatus);
374 nvkm_error(subdev, "%s - TP%d: %08x [%s]\n",
375 name, i, ustatus, msg);
376 ustatus = 0;
377 }
378 break;
379 case 8: /* PROP error */
380 if (display)
381 nv50_gr_prop_trap(
382 gr, ustatus_addr, ustatus, i);
383 ustatus = 0;
384 break;
385 }
386 if (ustatus) {
387 if (display)
388 nvkm_error(subdev, "%s - TP%d: Unhandled ustatus %08x\n", name, i, ustatus);
389 }
390 nvkm_wr32(device, ustatus_addr, 0xc0000000);
391 }
392
393 if (!tps && display)
394 nvkm_warn(subdev, "%s - No TPs claiming errors?\n", name);
395}
396
397static int
398nv50_gr_trap_handler(struct nv50_gr *gr, u32 display,
399 int chid, u64 inst, const char *name)
400{
401 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
402 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
403 u32 status = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400108);
404 u32 ustatus;
405 char msg[128];
406
407 if (!status && display) {
408 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP: no units reporting traps?\n");
409 return 1;
410 }
411
412 /* DISPATCH: Relays commands to other units and handles NOTIFY,
413 * COND, QUERY. If you get a trap from it, the command is still stuck
414 * in DISPATCH and you need to do something about it. */
415 if (status & 0x001) {
416 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400804) & 0x7fffffff;
417 if (!ustatus && display) {
418 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_DISPATCH - no ustatus?\n");
419 }
420
421 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00000000);
422
423 /* Known to be triggered by screwed up NOTIFY and COND... */
424 if (ustatus & 0x00000001) {
425 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400808);
426 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
427 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00001ffc);
428 u32 datal = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40080c);
429 u32 datah = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400810);
430 u32 class = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400814);
431 u32 r848 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400848);
432
433 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP DISPATCH_FAULT\n");
434 if (display && (addr & 0x80000000)) {
435 nvkm_error(subdev,
436 "ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] subc %d "
437 "class %04x mthd %04x data %08x%08x "
438 "400808 %08x 400848 %08x\n",
439 chid, inst, name, subc, class, mthd,
440 datah, datal, addr, r848);
441 } else
442 if (display) {
443 nvkm_error(subdev, "no stuck command?\n");
444 }
445
446 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400808, 0);
447 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4008e8, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x4008e8) & 3);
448 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400848, 0);
449 ustatus &= ~0x00000001;
450 }
451
452 if (ustatus & 0x00000002) {
453 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40084c);
454 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
455 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00001ffc);
456 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40085c);
457 u32 class = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400814);
458
459 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP DISPATCH_QUERY\n");
460 if (display && (addr & 0x80000000)) {
461 nvkm_error(subdev,
462 "ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] subc %d "
463 "class %04x mthd %04x data %08x "
464 "40084c %08x\n", chid, inst, name,
465 subc, class, mthd, data, addr);
466 } else
467 if (display) {
468 nvkm_error(subdev, "no stuck command?\n");
469 }
470
471 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40084c, 0);
472 ustatus &= ~0x00000002;
473 }
474
475 if (ustatus && display) {
476 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_DISPATCH "
477 "(unknown %08x)\n", ustatus);
478 }
479
480 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400804, 0xc0000000);
481 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x001);
482 status &= ~0x001;
483 if (!status)
484 return 0;
485 }
486
487 /* M2MF: Memory to memory copy engine. */
488 if (status & 0x002) {
489 u32 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x406800) & 0x7fffffff;
490 if (display) {
491 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
492 nv50_gr_trap_m2mf, ustatus);
493 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_M2MF %08x [%s]\n",
494 ustatus, msg);
495 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_M2MF %08x %08x %08x %08x\n",
496 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x406804),
497 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x406808),
498 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40680c),
499 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x406810));
500 }
501
502 /* No sane way found yet -- just reset the bugger. */
503 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400040, 2);
504 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400040, 0);
505 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406800, 0xc0000000);
506 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x002);
507 status &= ~0x002;
508 }
509
510 /* VFETCH: Fetches data from vertex buffers. */
511 if (status & 0x004) {
512 u32 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400c04) & 0x7fffffff;
513 if (display) {
514 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
515 nv50_gr_trap_vfetch, ustatus);
516 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_VFETCH %08x [%s]\n",
517 ustatus, msg);
518 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_VFETCH %08x %08x %08x %08x\n",
519 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400c00),
520 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400c08),
521 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400c0c),
522 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400c10));
523 }
524
525 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400c04, 0xc0000000);
526 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x004);
527 status &= ~0x004;
528 }
529
530 /* STRMOUT: DirectX streamout / OpenGL transform feedback. */
531 if (status & 0x008) {
532 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x401800) & 0x7fffffff;
533 if (display) {
534 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
535 nv50_gr_trap_strmout, ustatus);
536 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_STRMOUT %08x [%s]\n",
537 ustatus, msg);
538 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_STRMOUT %08x %08x %08x %08x\n",
539 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x401804),
540 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x401808),
541 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40180c),
542 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x401810));
543 }
544
545 /* No sane way found yet -- just reset the bugger. */
546 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400040, 0x80);
547 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400040, 0);
548 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x401800, 0xc0000000);
549 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x008);
550 status &= ~0x008;
551 }
552
553 /* CCACHE: Handles code and c[] caches and fills them. */
554 if (status & 0x010) {
555 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405018) & 0x7fffffff;
556 if (display) {
557 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg),
558 nv50_gr_trap_ccache, ustatus);
559 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_CCACHE %08x [%s]\n",
560 ustatus, msg);
561 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_CCACHE %08x %08x %08x %08x "
562 "%08x %08x %08x\n",
563 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405000),
564 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405004),
565 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405008),
566 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40500c),
567 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405010),
568 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405014),
569 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40501c));
570 }
571
572 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405018, 0xc0000000);
573 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x010);
574 status &= ~0x010;
575 }
576
577 /* Unknown, not seen yet... 0x402000 is the only trap status reg
578 * remaining, so try to handle it anyway. Perhaps related to that
579 * unknown DMA slot on tesla? */
580 if (status & 0x20) {
581 ustatus = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x402000) & 0x7fffffff;
582 if (display)
583 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP_UNKC04 %08x\n", ustatus);
584 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402000, 0xc0000000);
585 /* no status modifiction on purpose */
586 }
587
588 /* TEXTURE: CUDA texturing units */
589 if (status & 0x040) {
590 nv50_gr_tp_trap(gr, 6, 0x408900, 0x408600, display,
591 "TRAP_TEXTURE");
592 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x040);
593 status &= ~0x040;
594 }
595
596 /* MP: CUDA execution engines. */
597 if (status & 0x080) {
598 nv50_gr_tp_trap(gr, 7, 0x408314, 0x40831c, display,
599 "TRAP_MP");
600 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x080);
601 status &= ~0x080;
602 }
603
604 /* PROP: Handles TP-initiated uncached memory accesses:
605 * l[], g[], stack, 2d surfaces, render targets. */
606 if (status & 0x100) {
607 nv50_gr_tp_trap(gr, 8, 0x408e08, 0x408708, display,
608 "TRAP_PROP");
609 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x100);
610 status &= ~0x100;
611 }
612
613 if (status) {
614 if (display)
615 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP: unknown %08x\n", status);
616 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, status);
617 }
618
619 return 1;
620}
621
622void
623nv50_gr_intr(struct nvkm_gr *base)
624{
625 struct nv50_gr *gr = nv50_gr(base);
626 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
627 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
628 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
629 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400100);
630 u32 inst = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40032c) & 0x0fffffff;
631 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400704);
632 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
633 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00001ffc);
634 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400708);
635 u32 class = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400814);
636 u32 show = stat, show_bitfield = stat;
637 const struct nvkm_enum *en;
638 unsigned long flags;
639 const char *name = "unknown";
640 char msg[128];
641 int chid = -1;
642
643 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_inst(device->fifo, (u64)inst << 12, &flags);
644 if (chan) {
645 name = chan->object.client->name;
646 chid = chan->chid;
647 }
648
649 if (show & 0x00100000) {
650 u32 ecode = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400110);
651 en = nvkm_enum_find(nv50_data_error_names, ecode);
652 nvkm_error(subdev, "DATA_ERROR %08x [%s]\n",
653 ecode, en ? en->name : "");
654 show_bitfield &= ~0x00100000;
655 }
656
657 if (stat & 0x00200000) {
658 if (!nv50_gr_trap_handler(gr, show, chid, (u64)inst << 12, name))
659 show &= ~0x00200000;
660 show_bitfield &= ~0x00200000;
661 }
662
663 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, stat);
664 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
665
666 if (show) {
667 show &= show_bitfield;
668 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), nv50_gr_intr_name, show);
669 nvkm_error(subdev, "%08x [%s] ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] subc %d "
670 "class %04x mthd %04x data %08x\n",
671 stat, msg, chid, (u64)inst << 12, name,
672 subc, class, mthd, data);
673 }
674
675 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400824) & (1 << 31))
676 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400824, nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400824) & ~(1 << 31));
677
678 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(device->fifo, flags, &chan);
679}
680
681int
682nv50_gr_init(struct nvkm_gr *base)
683{
684 struct nv50_gr *gr = nv50_gr(base);
685 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
686 int ret, units, i;
687
688 /* NV_PGRAPH_DEBUG_3_HW_CTX_SWITCH_ENABLED */
689 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40008c, 0x00000004);
690
691 /* reset/enable traps and interrupts */
692 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400804, 0xc0000000);
693 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406800, 0xc0000000);
694 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400c04, 0xc0000000);
695 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x401800, 0xc0000000);
696 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405018, 0xc0000000);
697 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402000, 0xc0000000);
698
699 units = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001540);
700 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
701 if (!(units & (1 << i)))
702 continue;
703
704 if (device->chipset < 0xa0) {
705 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408900 + (i << 12), 0xc0000000);
706 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408e08 + (i << 12), 0xc0000000);
707 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408314 + (i << 12), 0xc0000000);
708 } else {
709 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408600 + (i << 11), 0xc0000000);
710 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408708 + (i << 11), 0xc0000000);
711 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40831c + (i << 11), 0xc0000000);
712 }
713 }
714
715 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0xffffffff);
716 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400138, 0xffffffff);
717 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0xffffffff);
718 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40013c, 0xffffffff);
719 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
720
721 /* upload context program, initialise ctxctl defaults */
722 ret = nv50_grctx_init(device, &gr->size);
723 if (ret)
724 return ret;
725
726 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400824, 0x00000000);
727 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400828, 0x00000000);
728 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40082c, 0x00000000);
729 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400830, 0x00000000);
730 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40032c, 0x00000000);
731 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400330, 0x00000000);
732
733 /* some unknown zcull magic */
734 switch (device->chipset & 0xf0) {
735 case 0x50:
736 case 0x80:
737 case 0x90:
738 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402ca8, 0x00000800);
739 break;
740 case 0xa0:
741 default:
742 if (device->chipset == 0xa0 ||
743 device->chipset == 0xaa ||
744 device->chipset == 0xac) {
745 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402ca8, 0x00000802);
746 } else {
747 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402cc0, 0x00000000);
748 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402ca8, 0x00000002);
749 }
750
751 break;
752 }
753
754 /* zero out zcull regions */
755 for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
756 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402c20 + (i * 0x10), 0x00000000);
757 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402c24 + (i * 0x10), 0x00000000);
758 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402c28 + (i * 0x10), 0x00000000);
759 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x402c2c + (i * 0x10), 0x00000000);
760 }
761
762 return 0;
763}
764
765int
766nv50_gr_new_(const struct nvkm_gr_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
767 int index, struct nvkm_gr **pgr)
768{
769 struct nv50_gr *gr;
770
771 if (!(gr = kzalloc(sizeof(*gr), GFP_KERNEL)))
772 return -ENOMEM;
773 spin_lock_init(&gr->lock);
774 *pgr = &gr->base;
775
776 return nvkm_gr_ctor(func, device, index, 0x00201000, true, &gr->base);
777}
778
779static const struct nvkm_gr_func
780nv50_gr = {
781 .init = nv50_gr_init,
782 .intr = nv50_gr_intr,
783 .chan_new = nv50_gr_chan_new,
784 .units = nv50_gr_units,
785 .sclass = {
786 { -1, -1, 0x0030, &nv50_gr_object },
787 { -1, -1, 0x502d, &nv50_gr_object },
788 { -1, -1, 0x5039, &nv50_gr_object },
789 { -1, -1, 0x5097, &nv50_gr_object },
790 { -1, -1, 0x50c0, &nv50_gr_object },
791 {}
792 }
793};
794
795int
796nv50_gr_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_gr **pgr)
797{
798 return nv50_gr_new_(&nv50_gr, device, index, pgr);
799}
